quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  21,58,"He shattered them all, except the biggest among them, that perhaps they may question it."
  21,59,"They said, “Who has done this to our Gods? He is indeed cruel!”"
  21,60,"Some among them said, “We heard a youth speak ill of them – the one called Ibrahim.”"
  21,61,"They said, “Therefore bring him in front of the people, perhaps they may testify.”"
  21,62,"They said, “Did you do this to our Gods, O Ibrahim?”"
  21,63,"Said he, “Rather, their chief may have done it; so question them, if they can speak.”"
  21,64,"So they turned towards their own selves and (inwardly) said, “Indeed you yourselves are unjust.”"
  21,65,"Again they were inverted upon their heads; saying, “You know well that these do not speak.”"
  21,66,"He said, “What! You worship, instead of Allah, one that neither benefits you nor harms you?”"
  21,67,"“Disgrace be upon you and all the idols whom you worship instead of Allah; so do you not have sense?”"
  21,68,"They said, “Burn him and help your Gods, if you want to.”"
  21,69,"We said, “O fire, become cool and peaceful upon Ibrahim.”"
  21,70,"And they wished to cause him harm, so We made them the greatest of losers."
  21,71,"And We rescued him and Lut towards the land which We have blessed for the entire world."
  21,72,"And We bestowed him Ishaq, and Yaqub the grandson; and We made all of them worthy of Our proximity."
